      "id": "PopularPost231267",
      "post_content": "Like it's ancestor [Primal Clay](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Primal Clay), this is one of the few really problematic cards I've seen with a characteristic ability.  \n  \nDesigners have complained about characteristic abilities -- things like \"[Mortivore](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mortivore)'s power and toughness are each equal to the number of creature cards in all graveyards,\" and, \"[Transguild Courier](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Transguild Courier) is all colors\" -- because they're not particularly intuitive. They describe a card's characteristics, apply in all zones, are continuously updated, and are applied before any other effects in the layer system. In effect, they're 'what's printed on the card, even if that can't be printed' (like the ever-changing number equaling Mortivore's power). At the same time, they're abilities that can be overwritten by things like [Humility](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Humility).   \n  \nThis can get weird in some edge cases. For example, if a Transguild Courier is subject to Humility, is it every color, or colorless? Or, if the only creatures in... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "longwinded",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost231267\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">Like it's ancestor <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Primal Clay\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Primal Clay\">Primal Clay</a>, this is one of the few really problematic cards I've seen with a characteristic ability.<br/><br/>Designers have complained about characteristic abilities -- things like \"<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mortivore\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mortivore\">Mortivore</a>'s power and toughness are each equal to the number of creature cards in all graveyards,\" and, \"<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Transguild Courier\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Transguild Courier\">Transguild Courier</a> is all colors\" -- because they're not particularly intuitive. They describe a card's characteristics, apply in all zones, are continuously updated, and are applied before any other effects in the layer system. In effect, they're 'what's printed on the card, even if that can't be printed' (like the ever-changing number equaling Mortivore's power). At the same time, they're abilities that can be overwritten by things like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Humility\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Humility\">Humility</a>. <br/><br/>This can get weird in some edge cases. For example, if a Transguild Courier is subject to Humility, is it every color, or colorless? Or, if the only creatures in... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 231267)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainConten